    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453033>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maxillary apparatus. A. Paucibranchia disjuncta n. comb. (Hartman, 1961), LACM-AHF POLY 6447, dorsal view; B. Marphysa viridis Treadwell, 1917, ECOSUR-P2678, dorsal view; C. Treadwellphysa yucatanensis Molina-Acevedo & Carrera-Parra, 2017, ECOSUR-P2811, dorsal view; D. Left MI-II-III-IV-V of P. disjuncta n. comb., dorsal view; E. Left MI- II-III-IV-V of M. viridis, dorsal view; F. Left MI-II-III-IV-V of T. yucatanensis, dorsal view. Scale bars: A, D, 0.4 mm; B, E, 0.45 mm; C, F, 0.25 mm. Dark and thin lines in D, E and F indicate the different forms in the MI of the apparatus of each species. fa= falcal arch, boe= basal outer edge, bie= basal inner edge, rp= rounded projection in base of MII." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453033/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453041>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Paucibranchia adenensis (Gravier, 1900) n. comb., non-type MNHN-A148. A. Parapodium 3; B. Parapodium 11; C. Parapodium 26; D. Parapodium 70; E. Parapodium 158; F. Parapodium 216. All in anterior view. Scale bars: A–F, 0.7 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453041/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453057>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Paucibranchia bellii (Audouin & Milne-Edwards, 1833) n. comb. A. Parapodium 3; B. Parapodium 29; C. Parapodium 46; D. Parapodium 93; E. Parapodium 138. All in anterior view. A, E from non-type MNHN-A39; B–D from lectotype MNHN TYPE 568. Scale bars: A, 140 µm; B, 180 µm; C, 160 µm; D, 111 µm; E, 230 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453057/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Paucibranchia adenensis (Gravier, 1900) n. comb., non-type MNHN-A148. A. Compound falciger, long blade, chaetiger, 11; B. Compound falciger, median blade, chaetiger, 11; C. Compound falciger, short blade, chaetiger, 216; D. Isodonts pectinate narrow with long and slender teeth, chaetiger 3; E. Isodonts pectinate narrow with short and slender teeth, chaetiger 216; F. Subacicular hook, distal end, chaetiger 158. Scale bars: A, 12.5 µm; B, 20 µm; C, F, 9.8 µm; D, 14 µm, E, 4.9 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453035>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Marphysa bonhardi McIntosh, 1885, holotype BMNH 1885.12.1.210. A. Anterior end, dorsal view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Aciculae, anterior chaetigers. Scale bars: A, 0.8 mm; B, C, 0.67 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453035/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1453153>
    dc:description "FIGURE 60. Paucibranchia purcellana (Willey, 1904) n. comb., holotype BNHM 1911.2.1.13. A. Anterior end with branchiae, lateral view; B. Anterior end, ventral view; C. Anterior end with branchiae, dorsal view; D. Pygidium. Scale bars: A, C, 3.6 mm; B, D, 1.8 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1453153/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

